All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
CleanData
Represents a cleaned and validated sensor reading, ready for storage after passing through the pipe-and-filter processing pipeline.
CleanDataRepository
Repository class responsible for persisting instances of CleanData into the database using JPA.
FileStorageVerticle
Verticle responsible for receiving validated data via the EventBus and persisting it to a local text file.
Main
Entry point of the application that coordinates the data processing pipeline.
MainVerticle
Main verticle that coordinates the deployment of all components in the Vert.x-based Pub/Sub monitoring pipeline.
ProducerBDVerticle
Verticle responsible for initiating a request to retrieve raw data (e.g., from a database or memory) and publishing each data item onto the EventBus channel "raw.data.incoming".
RawData
Represents a raw, unprocessed sensor reading retrieved directly from the data source, typically stored before any normalization, validation, or filtering is applied.
RawDataFilter
Defines a strategy interface for filtering or transforming RawData objects.
RawDataProcessingService
Service class responsible for orchestrating the processing of raw sensor data through a configurable pipeline of RawDataFilters and persisting valid results into the clean data repository.
RawDataRepository
Repository class responsible for accessing RawData entries from the raw_readings table in the database.
ReaderBDVerticle
Verticle that queries the database for RawData records and returns the result to requesting verticles via the EventBus.
